The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | SEHWAG IN NUMBERS
                                                                                                                       7                                      SEHWAG IN NUMBERS
                            
	 With his 12th four on Wednesday, Sehwag brought up the 1,000th boundary of his Test career. He becomes the third Indian to do so, after Sachin Tendulkar (1,786) and Rahul Dravid (1,444). Sehwag now has a total of 1,005 fours.         
	 As he chases his 21st century, on Thursday, Sehwag has scored 63.95% (or 4,494 runs) of his current total of 7,027 runs in boundaries and over boundaries. Of that, 4,020 have come in fours, and 474 in sixes.         
	m Sehwag became the 38th player overall, and the sixth Indian, to have scored 7,000 Test runs.         
	m Having achieved it in just 134 innings, Sehwag is now the second quickest player to reach the 7,000 mark.         
	The following is the list of the five fastest:               
	131 innings: Walter Hammond         
	134 innings: Sehwag         
	136 innings: Tendulkar         
	138 innings: Garfield Sobers         
	138 innings: Kumar Sangakkara               
